Title: City League Finals
Description:
Steve Colburn, Tournament Director. 
The Pandanet-AGA City League has been run for the last two years with players from all over the US and Canada. They have formed teams around cities and played on IGS to see who is the strongest city. This tournament has players from 1p to 13k within the three leagues. Full tournament information, players, and game records can be found on the Pandanet City League website. http://pandanet-igs.com/communities/agacityleague.html

Title: Facebook Open Go Simul
Description: Artificial Intelligence has taken go into new realms and this year at the US Go Congress attendees will be able to learn and improve their own games and have a lot of fun interacting with an AI. This Simul is a no-handicap teaching game with Facebook's OpenGo. OpenGo features a 20-0 record against top-30 professionals. Each player will be mailed an SGF file after the game along with annotations from OpenGo.

Title: Facebook Open Go - Pair Go with Pros
Description: Pair Go demonstration match with live commentary. Two Pros, each with Open Go as a Pair Go partner will face off.

Title: Departure
Description: Check out by 11 AM

Title: Lightning Go Tournament
Description: 19x19 played at lightning speed. Time limit 10 minutes each. No overtime. TD may declare a winner if player behind is playing uselessly trying to run out the clock.

Title: 9x9 Tournament
Description: Quick games played on a 9x9 board.

Title: 13x13 Tournament
Description: Quick games played on a 13x13 board.

Title: Youth Adult Pair Go
Description: Standard International Pair Go rules. 2 rounds at 4 team tables. 1 youth, 1 adult and 1 male the other female. Complaining about your partner’s play is strictly prohibited.

Title: Team Tournament
Description: Teams of three people will have 30 minutes per player, with 3 periods of 20 seconds byo-yomi. Prizes will be given to the best dan level and the best kyu level teams.
